      <div class="seo-concept-faq-list reveal">
        <details class="seo-concept-faq-item" open>
          <summary>How long does a custom WordPress build take?</summary>
          <p>Early concepts often appear in 2 weeks, while a full high-fidelity custom website usually builds over 5 to 7 weeks. Larger enterprise platforms or complex API integrations can take longer depending on technical depth.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="seo-concept-faq-item">
          <summary>Is WordPress secure enough for my business?</summary>
          <p>Yes, when built correctly. We implement enterprise-grade security hardening, two-factor authentication, and proactive malware monitoring to ensure your site is a fortress against digital threats.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="seo-concept-faq-item">
          <summary>Will I be able to edit the content myself?</summary>
          <p>Absolutely. We use Gutenberg and ACF Pro to build a custom editing interface that allows you to change text, images, and layouts easily without touching a single line of code.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="seo-concept-faq-item">
          <summary>How do you handle site speed and Core Web Vitals?</summary>
          <p>We build with a "lightweight first" philosophy. Our custom themes avoid heavy plugins and bloated page builders, ensuring your site passes Core Web Vitals with flying colors from day one.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="seo-concept-faq-item">
          <summary>Do you offer ongoing maintenance and support?</summary>
          <p>Yes. We offer monthly maintenance retainers that cover security updates, plugin audits, regular cloud backups, and active speed monitoring to keep your site at peak performance.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="seo-concept-faq-item">
          <summary>Can you migrate my site from Wix/Squarespace to WordPress?</summary>
          <p>Yes. We handle full migrations including content preservation, SEO redirection mapping (301s), and redesigning your assets within the more flexible WordPress ecosystem.</p>
        </details>
